race.comment: TASSORTING (4) improved again, narrowly beaten this track at Trip. The barrier is softer today and we are likely to see him back on speed. Locally trained, and Nolen is a key jockey switch. LAPLAND (3) is a local and also has winning claims. Placed three times in his initial preparation with the two most recent at Geelong. He's free running and jumps from the inside barrier. Ran a place at Moe at his only fresh outing and has jumped out twice. Has plenty of scope for improvement. The Freedmans have scratched a fancied stablemate and the debutant  BOLD SUITOR (11) resumes for a local stable following a promising maiden preparation. Has a low barrier and it's hard to fault his jumpout form at the track. Has upside and is ready to go. ARTIE'S STORM (7) stays in. He's had a thorough grounding and won his most recent jumpout. Has to be kept onside.
